Rating: 3
I was surprised at how good this was. I followed another reviewer's recommendation and fried up some chopped bacon until crispy, then gently fried the cabbage, which I had sliced,in the bacon fat with lots of black pepper and a bit of salt until cooked. I then added the crispy bacon at the end. For the meat sauce, I used ground beef only and fresh, rather than dried cranberries. I also added 2 tablespoons of tomato paste, 1 T of soy sauce to give it some depth, and the sweet/sour balance was perfect. However, I left it to cook on a slow simmer for an hour for the flavours to really blend. Kids loved it.

