Rating: 0
This was easy and delicious. Rather than pre-cook cabbage in broth, I fried 4 slices bacon (remove when crispy) and browned the 4 cabbage wedges on both sides in same skillet until golden brown. Remove; set aside in oven proof dish. Make sauce as directed (adding chicken stock at the end). Reduce slightly. Pour meat sauce over cabbage wedges; add back bacon and bake for about 1-1/2 hours or so (covered). This will be repeated and repeated! Thank you Gourmet!

